00:02:49.820 --> 00:02:54.000
So when we get into the workshop, we can show you how to do that, but you'll very commonly

38
00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:57.280
be using the compile and save a lot in this section.

39
00:02:57.280 --> 00:02:59.760
Number three is where your components live.

40
00:02:59.760 --> 00:03:03.840
So a blueprint, say it houses multiple components.

41
00:03:03.840 --> 00:03:09.760
So say you had a vehicle in your production and you wanted to add some headlights to that

42
00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:10.960
vehicle.

43
00:03:10.960 --> 00:03:13.980
So you'd add maybe two spotlights to that vehicle.

44
00:03:13.980 --> 00:03:16.480
Now the spotlights would be in this component list.

45
00:03:16.480 --> 00:03:21.480
So not only would the vehicle be there as a static mesh, the two headlights would then

46
00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:28.280
be there and you can see that any extra elements you're adding to that vehicle are all components.

47
00:03:28.280 --> 00:03:34.040
So say you added a separate door mesh or some kind of information inside the vehicle like

48
00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:36.520
some boxes or anything like this.

49
00:03:36.520 --> 00:03:39.940
These would all be components within this blueprint.

50
00:03:39.940 --> 00:03:43.380
Then you've got number four, which is your blueprint panel.

51
00:03:43.380 --> 00:03:46.260
So this is where all of your functions live.

52
00:03:46.260 --> 00:03:47.700
It's where all the inputs.

53
00:03:47.700 --> 00:03:52.360
So we've got both an event begin play, which fires at the very start of the game.

