63
00:04:22.600 --> 00:04:25.880
you need to drive some kind of gameplay conditions.

64
00:04:25.880 --> 00:04:30.500
Event dispatchers also live here and event dispatchers help with blueprint communication.

65
00:04:30.500 --> 00:04:34.360
It's almost like a message that gets sent out to another blueprint, which we will of

66
00:04:34.360 --> 00:04:36.380
course dig into.

67
00:04:36.380 --> 00:04:39.100
Number five is where all the main action is happening.

68
00:04:39.120 --> 00:04:43.820
This is where you're connecting your wires and your nodes to get the desired outcome.

69
00:04:43.820 --> 00:04:46.140
A few important things to point out here.

70
00:04:46.140 --> 00:04:50.200
Viewport will go to the visual view of what the blueprint is.

71
00:04:50.200 --> 00:04:54.540
So say going back to this vehicle example from your components on the left hand side,

72
00:04:54.540 --> 00:04:57.980
